{
  "texts": [
    "However, it is important to note issues related to the uniformity of scoring criteria and subjective awareness in the scoring process.",
    "Some datasets use human scoring to reflect preferences.",
    "Stack-Exchange-Preferences (Askell et al, 2021) is derived from StackOverflow, where each answer is assigned a score defined by Askell et al (2021).",
    "This score is based on the number of likes the answer receives and whether it is accepted by the question asker.",
    "In Summarize from Feedback (Stiennon et al, 2020), a portion of it involves scoring the quality of different answers using the Likert scale."
  ]
}